    <thetext>It would be helpful to have a Portal process to deactivate committers. I&apos;m not sure of everything that needs to happen when a committer is deactivated, but I would think most if not all of it could be automated.

Here&apos;s at least a partial list:

1. Foundation db is updated to deactivate person as committer.
2. Committer&apos;s account is deactivated.
3. Name and company of deactivated committer is added to dashboard database text file.
4. Etc.

A similar process could be implemented for suspended committers. After a certain period of time, perhaps a suspended committer would become a deactivated committer.</thetext>
